article.headline: Northeastern 61, Harvard 58
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Javorie Wilson scored 19 points, including 11 in the second half, as Northeastern beat Harvard 61-58 on Friday night. Jose Juan Barea hit three crucial free throws in the final minute as the Huskies fended off a Harvard comeback. Barea finished with 14 points and 8 assists for Northeastern (5-4) and Marcus Barnes added 12. David Giovacchini missed a last-second 3-point attempt as Harvard's comeback fell short. Michael Beal and Matt Stehle each scored 13 points to lead the Crimson (0-9). NU shot 32 percent in the first half, but scored 14 points off 12 Harvard turnovers to take a 29-27 lead at halftime. The Huskies took their largest lead of the game when Sylbrin Robinson slammed home a pass from Marcus Barnes to take a 48-38 lead with 9:40 left in the game. Robinson pulled down a game-high 13 rebounds. But Harvard, led by inside play of Stehle and Graham Beatty went on a 17-6 run to pull within one, 55-54, with 2:05 left. Barea sealed the win, hitting two free throws with 45 seconds left and assisting a Wilson layup that put Northeastern ahead 59-54.
